==============================
__How to book profits in our Trades..?✅

📈Many of you are new here and don’t know how to book profits in a trade and mostly are always confused about TPs.
Coz sometimes trades hit all TPs some hit 2-3 TPs and sometimes trades only hit TP1.

➡️ So…Here are two methods that you can use with our signals, which always keep you in profits ✅

1. First is trailing SL method, you always have to trail SL with profits and with each TP it means just trail SL in profits or at entry after hit TP1 and keep trailing it with each TP…don’t try to hodl without trailing SL till last TP or you will end-up with loss in cases of reversals🔺

2. Second is booking whole position at TP1, Just close your entire position at TP1 without any Greed of further profits.
We follow proper risk management and our SLs very small which is just 20-30% with leverage and our TP1 is also same as SL, and SL hits are very rare in comparison of TP1 hit.
So you will be always in profits even if you close 100% position at TP1✅

Choose one of above methods with our signals and you will always in profits with our Signals🚀

Hopefully now you will not spam in  DM about Hitting SL after TP hits🙂

Regards Admin__ ❤️

==============================
Dumps in the market occur simply due to :

- Funding high on futures and over leverage, so a reset cleans out the excess 

- Greedy late, FOMO buyers flushed

- Profit takers who brought early

Buying at the right time and not giving into greed emotion is very important

FACTS ABOUT INVESTMENT FOR THOSE WHO CAN'T FOLLOW MY SIGNALS


1. Professional Expertise: Investing in managed accounts or funds allows individuals who lack knowledge or experience in Crypto trading to leverage the expertise of professional traders. These professionals have a deep understanding of the market and employ proven strategies to generate potential profits.

2. Time-Saving: Crypto trading requires constant monitoring and analysis, which can be time-consuming for individuals with busy schedules. Investing in managed accounts or funds eliminates the need for active involvement, as the professionals handle all trading decisions on your behalf.

3. Diversification: Investing in Crypto through managed accounts or funds allows for diversification across different strategies or funds. This diversification can help reduce risk by spreading investments across various currency pairs and trading styles.

4. Risk Management: Professional traders managing the accounts or funds have experience in risk management. They employ strategies to mitigate potential losses and aim to preserve capital while seeking profitable opportunities.

5. Access to Global Markets: Crypto trading provides access to the largest financial market in the world, with trillions of dollars traded daily. Investing in managed accounts or funds allows individuals to tap into this global market without needing to navigate the complexities themselves.

6. Regulatory Compliance: Reputable providers of managed accounts or funds are regulated by financial authorities, ensuring compliance with industry standards and protecting investors' interests. This regulatory oversight adds an extra layer of security and transparency.

7. Performance Track Record: Before investing, individuals can review the performance track record of the managed accounts or funds they are considering. This historical data provides insight into past returns, risk levels, and consistency, helping investors make informed decisions.

8. Passive Income: Investing in managed accounts or funds can generate passive income for individuals who cannot actively trade Crypto themselves. As the professionals manage the trading activities, investors can potentially earn returns without dedicating their time and effort to trading.

9. Low Minimum Investment: Many managed accounts or funds have low minimum investment requirements, allowing individuals to access the Crypto market with a smaller initial capital compared to trading on their own. This affordability makes investing in Crypto more accessible to a wider range of investors.

10. Expert Monitoring: With managed accounts or funds, investors can benefit from ongoing monitoring and adjustments by professional traders. These experts continuously analyze market conditions, adjust strategies, and seize opportunities, optimizing the potential for returns.
